data.text:
Robin Williams was an actor and comedian who portrayed Walter Finch in the film Insomnia.

Williams rose to fame in the late seventies after appearing in Happy Days and Mork & Mindy as the alien Mork. He then moved on to acting in film projects from the eighties onwards, gaining much acclaim for his acting work. In 1997 he won the Academy Award for best supporting actor for the film Good Will Hunting.
